<span id="freeTextContainer812506395915195705">I liked this book, although it didn&apos;t tread the newest ground ever, the characters were interesting and the plot held my attention. I think the only thing lacking was the world building, it was confusing and I found it hard to really get a grasp on everything that was happening politically. BUT I recommend it highly, especially to people who like Robert Jordan, Joe Abercrombie, Stephen Erikson Robin Hobb or Terry Brooks. Very accessable, but with the new era &quot;grit&quot; we&apos;ve come to know and love in</span>
