        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2583190426" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2374471251445805081"><b>
  <i>My father once told me that delayed obedience is really disobedience.</i>
</b><br/><br/>3.5 stars, just rounded up, I made it 4 stars cause its more than a 3 star rating for me, its times like this that I hate that GR don&apos;t have a half rating. <br/><br/>The main reason why I rated this book like this is because the writing is terrible, its been a while I read a fantasy this badly written, its like it wasn&apos;t edited at all. The POV shift is the worst, you don&apos;t even know when its done until the character name is written. </span>
  <span id="freeText2374471251445805081" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>My father once told me that delayed obedience is really disobedience.</i>
</b><br /><br />3.5 stars, just rounded up, I made it 4 stars cause its more than a 3 star rating for me, its times like this that I hate that GR don't have a half rating. <br /><br />The main reason why I rated this book like this is because the writing is terrible, its been a while I read a fantasy this badly written, its like it wasn't edited at all. The POV shift is the worst, you don't even know when its done until the character name is written. <br /><br /><b>
  <i>“Assassination is an art, milord, and I am the city’s most accomplished artist.”</i>
</b><br /><br />Moving on to things I like about this book, the plot is awesome but it wasn't well portrayed, I feel like the author didn't use all the tools available to him. The world building is average, I've read better ones, but I let that pass cause its a debut novel, reading this made me realize how far Brent Weeks has come cause his <i>Lightbringer</i> series is better. The characters aren't all bad, I'm hoping for some character development in book two. The fight scenes were okay and sadly the magic system were not well depicted, another development I'm hoping will improve.<br /><br /><b>
  <i>“Life is empty. Life is meaningless. When we take a life, we aren’t taking anything of value. Wetboys are killers. That’s all we do. That’s all we are. There are no poets in the bitter business.”</i>
</b><br /><br />The above quote all but summarises the mind of the assassins in this book. This book is about assassination, politics and friendship .<br /><br />The plot is mainly about a country called Ceneria, Azoth is the protagonist of this book but they are also other characters with POVs in this book. Azoth grew up in the Warrens fancy name for slums. Azoth, Jarl and Doll Girl but something something bad happened and they went their seperate way. Azoth became an apprentice to Durzo Blint an assassin know as wetboy due to his ability to use magic <i> all assassins with magic are called wetboy which I think is ridiculous, wetboy sound silly</i><br /><br /><b>
  <i>Cruelty walked the Warrens holding hands with poverty and rage.</i>
</b><br /><br />It was a bad time to be a famous assassin's apprentice cause war is coming and they must pick a side.<br /><br />Some of the other characters that I love are Logan Gyre who is a very humble and kind nobleman, Count Drake, Momma K and the Drake girls.<br /><br /><br /></span>
